PART II — SCRAPED DATA OWNERSHIP
=============================================================================

4. NO OWNERSHIP OF SCRAPED CONTENT

   Neither the authors of this Software nor its users acquire any
   ownership, copyright, or intellectual property rights over content
   collected using this Software ("Scraped Content"), by the mere act
   of scraping.

   To be unambiguously clear:

     a) Scraping content does NOT transfer ownership.
     b) Scraping content does NOT create a new copyright.
     c) Scraping content does NOT grant a license to use that content.
     d) Aggregating or reformatting scraped content does NOT create
        new rights over the underlying content.

5. ORIGINAL RIGHTS PRESERVED

   ALL rights in Scraped Content — including copyright, trademark,
   database rights, moral rights, and any other intellectual property
   rights — belong to, and remain with, the original authors, creators,
   publishers, and/or rights holders.

   This applies to all types of content: text, images, photographs,
   audio, video, code, databases, structured data, trademarks, and
   brand elements.

6. USER RESPONSIBILITY

   Users of this Software are solely responsible for:

     a) Ensuring they have the legal right to scrape, store, process,
        and/or redistribute any content they collect.
     b) Complying with applicable laws (copyright, GDPR, CCPA, CFAA,
        terms of service, etc.).
     c) Respecting robots.txt where configured to do so.
     d) Properly attributing and citing original sources.
     e) Honoring takedown requests from rights holders.

7. COMMUNITY DATASET

   The community dataset at:
     https://huggingface.co/datasets/ray0rf1re/Site.scraped

   Is community-contributed. The maintainer (ray0rf1re / minerofthesoal)
   does NOT own contributed content. All rights remain with original
   creators. Contributors are responsible for their uploads. Rights
   holders may request removal via the GitHub issue tracker.

8. CITATIONS

   Auto-generated citations (MLA 9th / APA 7th) are provided to assist
   with attribution. They may contain errors and must be verified. They
   do not constitute legal permission to use cited content.

